-- Argentina to appeal U.S. judge's order calling bond payment illegal
-- By Nate Raymond in New York
-- Fri Aug 29, 2014 06:24PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Aug 29 (Reuters) - Argentina said on Friday it would appeal a U.S. judge's decision declaring a $539 million payment the country deposited with Bank of New York Mellon Corp <BK.N> for its restructured bondholders illegal.

